  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bca\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b9c\u0ba9\u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b86\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0ba4 \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b86\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b86\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0baf \u0ba4\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd - \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba9\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sumanthran ready to explore support for non-PDP-dominated national government",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "Tamil National Alliance member of parliament Sumanthran said that if the government makes honest efforts to form a government of national parties that are not dominated by the PDP, the TNA will consider supporting such efforts.",
        "The Tamil National Federation has expressed its willingness to join an all-party government if the government makes sincere efforts to form a government of national parties that is not dominated by the Popular People's Party, the Tamil National Federation will consider supporting such efforts, the Sunday Times reported that Tamil National Federation Member of Parliament Sumanthran said.",
        "Sumanthran said that we are opposing the current government because it will become another government led by Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna, which has lost its political mandate.",
        "Sumanthran mentioned that the people have rejected the Sri Lanka People's Party, and because of this, the President and the Prime Minister, who were elected by the party, have resigned from their positions.",
        "He further stated that an all-party government should be formed that includes the other opposition parties in the Parliament, he further stated that any attempt to form a national government should not be led by Sri Lanka Budujana Peramuna and we are following the position that that party should not dominate."
      ],
